						               													<description>From the promotional packaging inside of Zitadelle, viewable in Image 138790.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;An interesting and varied board game.  Like in the game Halma, players must get their pieces into an opposite field.  However, the way to get there is over a turntable that one is allowed to turn one quarter, so long as there is another piece in the goal.  That is how the fortune of the party will most change.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game rules:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game can be played with up to 4 players.&amp;#10;Each player gets 10 meeples, of which 6 are &amp;#10;to be moved into the opposite destination spaces &amp;#10;of the same color.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The starting player is determined by chance.&amp;#10;The meeples can jump over other meeples of the same &amp;#10;or any other color to get to the destination &amp;#10;spaces (jumping is done like in the Halma game).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every time a player gets one of his meeples on a &amp;#10;destination space, the turntable gets turned a quarter&amp;#10;turn to the right.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This provides for variety in the gameplay, because &amp;#10;every turn changes the position of the meeples &amp;#10;for every player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is the player, who is the first to get 6&amp;#10;meeples on the destination spaces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The 4 remaining meeples are without importance for the&amp;#10;outcome of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Note: This game is played without a die.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
